ACTRESS Zola Nombona is leaving Generations: The Legacy. Zola has been playing Pamela Khoza, Siyanda Khoza’s estranged wife in the SABC1 soapie since last May. Her manager Ntando Zikalala confirmed the news of her departure, saying: “Yes, she’s definitely leaving the soapie.” Ntando said Zola was serving her notice and had received new offers. “The reason for her departure is she got new offers she wants to try out.” In October, Zola wrote a long post on social media about her journey with the soapie. ALSO READ | Thando Thabethe makes fire move at Miss SA! “What a journey. I’ve been with the Generations family for more than six months now and what a lovely journey it has been,” she said. “I thought I was not a long-form actor because I get bored easily, but I quickly realised I actually didn’t have the stamina for it (yep, acting stamina is a real thing).” She said: “I got the opportunity to test my acting stamina in theatre productions, but that hasn’t happened in a while so beku rough.”